\delta, \epsilon
 \lim_{x\to -2} (2x^2+5x+3)= 1 
|2x^2 + 5x + 3 - 1| < \epsilon
|(2x + 1)(x + 2)| < \epsilon
|(2x + 4 - 3)(x + 2)| < \epsilon
|(2(x+2)^2 -3(x + 2)| \leq 2|x+2|^2 +3|x + 2| < \epsilon
|x+2| < 1
\delta=\min\left(\dfrac{\epsilon}{5}, 1\right)
\lim_{x\to -2} (3x^2+4x-2)= 2
|3x^2 + 4x - 2 - 2| < \epsilon
|3x^2 - 12 + 4x + 8| < \epsilon
|3(x+2)(x-2) + 4(x + 2)| < \epsilon
|3(x+2)(x + 2 -4) + 4(x + 2)| < \epsilon
|3[(x+2)^2 -4(x+2)] + 4(x + 2)| < \epsilon
|3(x+2)^2 - 8(x+2)| \leq 3|x+2|^2 + 8|x+2| < \epsilon
|x + 2| < 1
\delta  =\min\left(\dfrac{\epsilon}{11}, 1\right)
|x+2| < 1
\delta \leq 1
\delta \geq 1
|x+2| \geq 1
 \lim_{x\to -2} (2x^2+5x+3)= 1 
|(2x + 1)(x + 2)| < \epsilon
|x - (-2)| < \delta 
\delta = 3
|x+2| < 3 \Rightarrow -5 < x < 1 \Rightarrow -9 < 2x + 1 < 3
|2x + 1||x + 2| < 3 \cdot |x + 2| < \epsilon \Rightarrow |x+2| < \frac{\epsilon}{3} 
